              "uco-observable:stringValue": "Query Reports Utilities Help Log Out\n\nCLOSED,MULTI,PROTO,SUPERS\n\nU.S. District Court\nEastern District of Louisiana (New Orleans)\nCRIMINAL DOCKET FOR CASE #: 2:22-cr-00115-ILRL-KWR All Defendants\n\nCase title: USA v. Keel et al Date Filed: 06/02/2022\n\nMagistrate judge case number: 2:22-mj-00062-DM Date Terminated: 10/25/2023\n\nAssigned to: Judge Ivan L.R. Lemelle\nReferred to: Magistrate Judge Karen Wells Roby\n\nDefendant (1)\nChristopher L. Keel represented by Christopher L. Keel\nTERMINATED: 10/25/2023 03691-510\nJESUP\nFEDERAL CORRECTIONAL INSTITUTION (FSL)\nInmate Mail/Parcels\n2600 HIGHWAY 301 SOUTH\nJESUP, GA 31599\nPRO SE\n\nValerie Welz Jusselin\nFederal Public Defender (New Orleans)\nHale Boggs Federal Building\n500 Poydras St.\nRoom 318\nNew Orleans, LA 70130\n504-589-7930\nEmail: valerie_jusselin@fd.org\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: Public Defender Appointment\n\nClaude J. Kelly\nFederal Public Defender's Office\nHale Boggs Federal Building\n500 Poydras Street\nRoom 318\nNew Orleans, LA 70130\n504-589-7939\nEmail: claude_kelly@fd.org\nTERMINATED: 06/03/2022\nDesignation: Public Defender Appointment\n\nPending Counts Disposition\n18:1349 CONSPIRACY TO COMMIT WIRE FRAUD\nSentencing held on 10/25/2023\n(1s)\n18:912 FALSE PERSONATION OF AN EMPLOYEE OR\nOFFICER OF THE UNITED STATES and 18:2 AIDING AND\nSentencing held on 10/25/2023\nABETTING\n(2s)\n\nHighest Offense Level (Opening)\nFelony\n\nTerminated Counts Disposition\n18:1349 CONSPIRACY TO COMMIT WIRE FRAUD\nDismissed on 10/26/2023\n(1)\n18:912 FALSE PERSONATION OF AN EMPLOYEE OR\nOFFICER OF THE UNITED STATES and 18:2 AIDING AND\nDismissed on 10/26/2023\nABETTING\n(2)\n\nHighest Offense Level (Terminated)\nFelony\n\nComplaints Disposition\n18:912 and 18:2 Impersonation of an officer or employee of the\nUnited States; 18:1343 and 18:1349 Conspiracy to Commit\nWire fraud\n\nAssigned to: Judge Ivan L.R. Lemelle\nReferred to: Magistrate Judge Karen Wells Roby\n\nDefendant (2)\nJayesh J Panchal represented by Claude J. Kelly\nTERMINATED: 09/06/2023 (See above for address)\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: Public Defender Appointment\n\nCynthia Marie Cimino\nBrowneLaw LLC\n3330 West Esplanade South\nSuite 302\nMetairie, LA 70002\n504-648-0171\nFax: 504-285-4093\nEmail: ccimino@brownelaw.com\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: CJA Appointment\n\nPending Counts Disposition\nNone\n\nHighest Offense Level (Opening)\nNone\n\nTerminated Counts Disposition\n18:1349 CONSPIRACY TO COMMIT WIRE FRAUD\nDismissed on 9/5/2023\n(1)\n18:912 FALSE PERSONATION OF AN EMPLOYEE OR\nOFFICER OF THE UNITED STATES and 18:2 AIDING AND\nDismissed on 9/5/2023\nABETTING\n(2)\n\nHighest Offense Level (Terminated)\nFelony\n\nComplaints Disposition\nNone\n\nPlaintiff\nUSA represented by Matthew Richard Payne\nU. S. Attorney's Office (New Orleans)\n650 Poydras St.\nSuite 1600\nNew Orleans, LA 70130\n504-680-3081\nFax: 504-589-4014\nEmail: matthew.payne@usdoj.gov\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: Assistant U.S. Attorney\n\nDate Filed # Docket Text\n04/29/2022 1 COMPLAINT signed by Magistrate Judge Dana Douglas as to Christopher L. Keel (1). (Attachments: # 1 Criminal Magistrate Case Sheet)\n(2cc: USM)(plh) [2:22-mj-00062-DM] (Entered: 05/02/2022)\n05/26/2022 3 EXPARTE/CONSENT MOTION for Writ of Habeas Corpus ad prosequendum by USA as to Christopher L. Keel. (Attachments: # 1\nProposed Order)(Payne, Matthew) [2:22-mj-00062-DM] (Entered: 05/26/2022)\n05/27/2022 4 ORDER GRANTING 3 Motion for Writ of Habeas Corpus ad prosequendum as to Christopher L. Keel (1). Signed by Magistrate Judge\nMichael North on 5/27/2022. (jls) [2:22-mj-00062-DM] (Entered: 05/27/2022)\n05/27/2022 5 Writ of Habeas Corpus ad Prosequendum Issued. (jls) (3cc: USM, cc: Crim Mag) [2:22-mj-00062-DM] (Entered: 05/27/2022)\n06/01/2022 6 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Dana Douglas:Initial Appearance as to Christopher L. Keel held on 6/1/2022.\nDefendant remanded. Detention Hearing set for 6/3/2022 10:00 AM before Duty Magistrate. Preliminary Hearing set for 6/14/2022 02:00\nPM before Duty Magistrate. (Court Reporter Magistrate Clerical.) (plh) [2:22-mj-00062-DM] (Entered: 06/01/2022)\n06/01/2022 7 ORDER APPOINTING FEDERAL PUBLIC DEFENDER as to Christopher L. Keel. Claude J. Kelly for Christopher L. Keel appointed.\nSigned by Magistrate Judge Dana Douglas on 6/1/2022. (plh) [2:22-mj-00062-DM] (Entered: 06/01/2022)\n06/01/2022 8 CJA 23 Financial Affidavit by Christopher L. Keel (plh) [2:22-mj-00062-DM] (Entered: 06/01/2022)\n06/02/2022 9 PRETRIAL BAIL REPORT as to Christopher L. Keel. NOTE: The attached document will only be accessible to the criminal duty judge,\nthe government attorney and the attorney for the applicable defendant for bail determination proceedings. After the proceedings are\ncompleted, only Probation will have access. (Robert, Cheryl) [2:22-mj-00062-DM] (Entered: 06/02/2022)\n06/02/2022 10 INDICTMENT as to Christopher L. Keel (1) count(s) 1, 2. (Attachments: # 1 Criminal Magistrate Case Sheet, # 2 Criminal Defendant\nInformation Sheet) (dw) (Entered: 06/02/2022)\n06/02/2022 13 NOTICE OF HEARING as to Christopher L. Keel. Arraignment set for 6/3/2022 at 10:00 AM before Duty Magistrate. (dw) (Entered:\n06/02/2022)\n06/03/2022 14 Minute Entry for proceedings held on 6/3/2022 before Magistrate Judge Dana Douglas as to Christopher L. Keel: Added attorney Valerie\nWelz Jusselin for Christopher L. Keel. For reasons stated on the record, defendant was not present. Ms. Kuhn requested a continuance of\nthe arraignment and detention hearing for reasons stated on the record. There was no objection by the government. Arraignment set for\n6/8/2022 at 2:00 PM before Duty Magistrate. Detention Hearing set for 6/8/2022 at 2:00 PM before Duty Magistrate. (Court Reporter\nMagistrate Clerical.) (dw) (Entered: 06/03/2022)\n06/03/2022 15 NOTICE OF HE